main event: Three witnesses reported seeing a bright light that changed colors and moved below the horizon in Cincinnati, Ohio on July 9, 1968.
interesting points: The light was about two intensities of Jupiter and changed colors between white, blue, and red., The observation duration was one hour., The object moved in a secondary direction towards the west., The Air Force indicated that the description was consistent with a star or planet but insufficient for scientific investigation., The witnesses reported physical evidence but did not provide sufficient data for further analysis.
witness description: three observers who saw the phenomenon in the sky
